 <text>
  <front>
   <head>To Mrs. Boteler. A Description of her Garden.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">charming is this little Spot</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Dispos'd with Art and Taste.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A thousand Beauties intermix'd,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Prepare the Eyes a Feast.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The lovely  in ample Rows,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With  climbing round,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A shining Gravel Walk inclose.</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Where not a  is found.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The ,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And  sweet, I sing;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And fragrant purple ,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">All Harbingers of .</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The musky lovely blushing ,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">with rich Perfume;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">that vie with ,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And  annual Bloom.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Th'immortal , fair ,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And beamy ,</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And  (lovely Tribe!)</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Their various Blooms unfold.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Gard'ner's Pride ,</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">ethereal blue,</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The , and golden ,</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Wonder of .</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="7" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The , as Poets sing,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">That  deign'd to wear,</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That in  Gardens spring,</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Bloom fair and fragrant here.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="8" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The  fair as new fall'n Snow;</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">All these the Borders grace.</l>
     <l n="31" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And ,</l>
     <l n="32" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With Fragrance fill the Place.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="9" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="33" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A Groop of dwarfish  Trees</l>
     <l n="34" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Appear, a fairy Scene,</l>
     <l n="35" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Loaden with Fruit, such  gave</l>
     <l n="36" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">To , Beauty's Queen.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="10" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="37" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Stately the rising Mount appears,</l>
     <l n="38" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With tow'ring  o'erspread;</l>
     <l n="39" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Whose gently waving Branches form,</l>
     <l n="40" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">At Noon, a cooling Shade.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="11" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="41" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The  Plant the Victors crown,</l>
     <l n="42" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And  by Poets worn;</l>
     <l n="43" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The party-colour'd ,</l>
     <l n="44" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And  perfuming .</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="12" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="45" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">These line the Walks, and make the Bounds</l>
     <l n="46" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">All verdant young, and fair:</l>
     <l n="47" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">All speak the Owner's Judgment good,</l>
     <l n="48" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And praise the Gard'ner's Care.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="13" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="49" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Faint Emblem of a fairer Mind,</l>
     <l n="50" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">That over all presides:</l>
     <l n="51" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For ev'ry Virtue's planted there,</l>
     <l n="52" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And ev'ry Action guides.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
